    cte.push_scope();
    ...
    Expr::StmtBlock(exprs.clone(), *span).to_c(cte, ctx);
    cte.pop_scope();
    ...
}
```

But in `pre_transpile`, `StmtBlockWithScope` does NOT push a scope — it just iterates. The scope is managed by the caller (`DeclareFunction`). So `#x: i32;` should be declared in the function's scope (scope 1).

